      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term \"fake news\" has largely evolved into a weaponized rhetorical tool used primarily to dismiss information that contradicts a person's political ideology rather than to identify objectively false content. This shift allows bad actors to label legitimate investigative journalism as \"fake\" simply because it challenges their preferred narrative, effectively silencing dissent without needing to prove the facts are wrong. Consequently, the public discourse is now dominated by a culture of dismissal where the credibility of a source is decided by its political alignment rather than its accuracy or integrity.",
